<emphasis box="[789,972,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="493">Pareas berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A. The three “young” specimens mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[184,359,1904,1928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="493" pagination="4 - 67" refId="ref7393" refString="Theobald, W. (1868 a) Catalogue of the Reptiles of British Birma, embracing the Provinces of Pegu, Martaban, and Tenasserim; with descriptions of new or little-known species. Journal of the Linnean Society, London, Zoology, 10 (1), 4 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1868. tb 02007. x" type="journal article" year="1868">Theobald (1868a</bibRefCitation>
–b), original syntypes of both of 
<taxonomicName box="[699,891,1904,1928]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macularius">
<emphasis box="[699,891,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="493">Pareas macularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority=", ZSI" authorityName="ZSI" box="[943,1177,1904,1928]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[943,1126,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="493">Pareas berdmorei</emphasis>
, ZSI
</taxonomicName>
8024, ZSI 8025 and ZSI 8026.—B. The two “adult” specimens mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[701,877,1940,1964]" pageId="3" pageNumber="493" pagination="4 - 67" refId="ref7393" refString="Theobald, W. (1868 a) Catalogue of the Reptiles of British Birma, embracing the Provinces of Pegu, Martaban, and Tenasserim; with descriptions of new or little-known species. Journal of the Linnean Society, London, Zoology, 10 (1), 4 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1868. tb 02007. x" type="journal article" year="1868">Theobald (1868a</bibRefCitation>
–b), ZSI 8021 and ZSI 8022 (top and centre), original syntypes of both of 
<taxonomicName box="[356,548,1976,2000]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macularius">
<emphasis box="[356,548,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="493">Pareas macularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[598,780,1976,2000]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="493" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[598,780,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="493">Pareas berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as specimen ZSI 8023 (bottom) that does not belong to the type series of either of these species. Photographs by Kaushik Deuti.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="494" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">
There have been some confusion in the literature about the type series of 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1232,151,177]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[1031,1232,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">Pareas berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Das, I. &amp; Datta Gupta, B. &amp; Gayen, N. C." pageId="4" pageNumber="494" pagination="121 - 172" refId="ref6431" refString="Das, I., Datta Gupta, B. &amp; Gayen, N. C. (1998) History and catalogue of reptiles types in the collection of the Zoological Survey of India. Journal of South Asian Natural History, 3 (2), 121 - 172." type="journal article" year="1998">
Das 
<emphasis box="[1298,1348,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">et al</emphasis>
. (1998: 150)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<specimenCount box="[342,507,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">three syntypes</specimenCount>
, ZSI 8021 to ZSI 8023. The description of this taxon by 
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[1154,1356,187,214]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" pagination="8 - 88" refId="ref7466" refString="Theobald, W. (1868 b) Catalogue of Reptiles in the Museum of the Asiatic Society of Bengal. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 37, Extra number, pp. i - vi + [7] + 8 - 88 + i - iii (Appendix), pls. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1868">Theobald (1868b)</bibRefCitation>
makes clear that it was based on two “adult” specimens. We examined these specimens, still extant and in good condition. Only ZSI 8021 and ZSI 8022 are adult animals, as correctly stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhosale, H. &amp; Phansalkar, P. &amp; Sawant, M. &amp; Gowande, G. &amp; Patel, H. &amp; Mirza, Z. A." box="[951,1193,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" pagination="54 - 73" refId="ref6174" refString="Bhosale, H., Phansalkar, P., Sawant, M., Gowande, G., Patel, H. &amp; Mirza, Z. A. (2020) A new species of snail-eating snakes of the genus Pareas Wagler, 1830 (Reptilia: Serpentes) from eastern Himalayas, India. European Journal of Taxonomy, 729 (1), 54 - 73. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2020.729.1191" type="journal article" year="2020">
Bhosale 
<emphasis box="[1049,1100,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
. Specimen ZSI 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.023208" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" unit="mm" value="8023208.0">8023, 208 mm</quantity>
long (SVL: 
<quantity box="[390,488,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.66" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" unit="mm" value="166.0">166 mm</quantity>
; TaL: 
<quantity box="[561,645,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" unit="mm" value="42.0">42 mm</quantity>
; examined), is a juvenile or perhaps a neonate (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1278,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[401,1263,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[151,1436,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. The original syntypes of Pareas macularius and Pareas berdmorei. A. The three “young” specimens mentioned by Theobald (1868a–b), original syntypes of both of Pareas macularius and Pareas berdmorei, ZSI 8024, ZSI 8025 and ZSI 8026.—B. The two “adult” specimens mentioned by Theobald (1868a–b), ZSI 8021 and ZSI 8022 (top and centre), original syntypes of both of Pareas macularius and Pareas berdmorei, as well as specimen ZSI 8023 (bottom) that does not belong to the type series of either of these species. Photographs by Kaushik Deuti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6333759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6333759/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). It cannot be considered one of the 
<typeStatus box="[398,496,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[534,676,331,357]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[534,676,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">
According to the way in which 
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[553,755,367,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" pagination="8 - 88" refId="ref7466" refString="Theobald, W. (1868 b) Catalogue of Reptiles in the Museum of the Asiatic Society of Bengal. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 37, Extra number, pp. i - vi + [7] + 8 - 88 + i - iii (Appendix), pls. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1868">Theobald (1868b)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[876,1077,367,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[876,1077,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">Pareas berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its type material, this taxon could have been considered either a junior objective synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1028,403,429]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macularius">
<emphasis box="[875,1028,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. macularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a replacement name for this latter taxon. However, the type series of 
<taxonomicName box="[543,687,439,465]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[543,687,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is obviously composed of specimens referable to two distinct species easy to diagnose. In their revision, 
<bibRefCitation author="Poyarkov, N. A. &amp; Nguyen, T. V. &amp; Pawangkhanant, P. &amp; Yushchenko, P. V. &amp; Brakels, P. &amp; Nguyen, L. H. &amp; Nguyen, H. N. &amp; Suwannapoom, C. &amp; Orlov, N. &amp; Vogel, G." box="[594,846,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref7137" refString="Poyarkov, N. A., Nguyen, T. V., Pawangkhanant, P., Yushchenko, P. V., Brakels, P., Nguyen, L. H., Nguyen, H. N., Suwannapoom, C., Orlov, N. &amp; Vogel, G. (2022) An integrative taxonomic revision of Slug-eating Snakes (Squamata: Pareidae: Pareineae) reveals unprecedented diversity in Indochina. PeerJ, 10 (e 12713) 1 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 12713" type="journal article" year="2022">
Poyarkov 
<emphasis box="[708,757,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">et al</emphasis>
. (2022)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName box="[995,1137,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[995,1137,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. berdmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not a replacement name of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,335,511,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macularius">
<emphasis box="[181,335,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. macularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a junior synonym of this latter species but a valid species, distinct from both 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1382,511,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macularius">
<emphasis box="[1229,1382,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. macularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, also 
<taxonomicName box="[203,336,547,572]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis box="[203,336,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at species level. In order to fix the nomenclatural status at species level of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Poyarkov et al. (2022: 47)" authorityName="Poyarkov" authorityPageNumber="47" authorityYear="2022" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">
<emphasis box="[1173,1316,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">P. berdmorei</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Poyarkov, N. A. &amp; Nguyen, T. V. &amp; Pawangkhanant, P. &amp; Yushchenko, P. V. &amp; Brakels, P. &amp; Nguyen, L. H. &amp; Nguyen, H. N. &amp; Suwannapoom, C. &amp; Orlov, N. &amp; Vogel, G." pageId="4" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref7137" refString="Poyarkov, N. A., Nguyen, T. V., Pawangkhanant, P., Yushchenko, P. V., Brakels, P., Nguyen, L. H., Nguyen, H. N., Suwannapoom, C., Orlov, N. &amp; Vogel, G. (2022) An integrative taxonomic revision of Slug-eating Snakes (Squamata: Pareidae: Pareineae) reveals unprecedented diversity in Indochina. PeerJ, 10 (e 12713) 1 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 12713" type="journal article" year="2022">
Poyarkov 
<emphasis box="[151,200,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">et al</emphasis>
. (2022: 47)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
selected a 
<typeStatus box="[452,555,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this species (see below). In order to fix the status of 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1390,583,609]" class="Reptilia" family="Pareatidae" genus="Pareas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macularius">
<emphasis box="[1179,1390,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">Pareas macularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we here select a 
<typeStatus box="[297,400,619,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="494">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
